# Cursor Rules — jodl-workspace

## Brain (shared across ALL models)
Read D:\.agents\BRAIN.md at session start. Load relevant files only.

### Confidence tiers
- experiments/ — write before bold moves
- staging/     — new learnings this session
- mistakes/    — confirmed failures
- patterns/    — proven 2+ sessions

### After every brain write
Run in terminal: `cd D:\.agents && git add -A && git commit -m "brain: <change>"`

## Stack
- pnpm workspaces + Turborepo
- TypeScript 6, moduleResolution: bundler, ignoreDeprecations: "6.0"
- Vite 8 (apps), tsup (packages)
- React 19, GSAP, Framer Motion, Lenis ^1.3.0
- React Three Fiber + Three.js (jodlxverse)

## Architecture
```
packages/  @jodl/tokens @jodl/motion @jodl/typography @jodl/ui @jodl/patterns @jodl/hooks @jodl/system
apps/      @jodl/app-sarta @jodl/app-creat-studio @jodl/app-jodlxverse
tools/     @jodl/cli
```

## Pattern promotion path
apps/[app]/features/ → jodl-system/sources/ → jodl-system/patterns/ → registry/components.json → @jodl/patterns/

## Quality gate (before any pattern enters registry)
- 3 viewports visual check
- Only @jodl/tokens — no inline styles
- prefers-reduced-motion respected
- keyboard + aria
- GPU-composited animations
- _meta.yaml complete

## Never
- Import from D:\SARTA\sarta-store\ (old) — use D:\jodl-workspace\apps\sarta\
- Use lenis@^2.0.0 — doesn't exist
- Add better-sqlite3 without C++ build tools installed first
- Push to @jodl/patterns without quality gate pass
